<!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  When I rerolled Didi into a mage, I certainly didn't hesitate to head to Paludal at 6 (yes, you can hunt there from 6, just not bandits), and take advantage of the massive XP to get a fast headstart on my new career.  <br>
<br>
I don't believe that getting fast XP necessarily hurts the development of your character.  I have other characters on this and other servers, and just because they could get from 6 to 26 in a week by sitting in Paludal, doesn't mean they don't have strong personalities of their own (as I think anybody who has met them will agree).  Equally, lingering around the Oasis for weeks doesn't necessarily mean they will develop personality, maybe they'll just get frustrated.<br>
<br>
The fast XP in Paludal is a bit worrying when it comes to newbies who advance so fast they never learn how to play their class sensibly, and end up at 30 without a clue how to play or be a respectful group member.  But I think those inclined to be roleplayers will be roleplayers anyway, and those who won't, won't.<br>
<br>
I do think that PoP had a catastrophic effect on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>atmosphere</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of the game despite the convenience.  But again I don't think it affects roleplay so much, except insofar that it's now so easy to travel that you're unlikely to meet the same person in the same place two nights in a row so it's hard to build up ongoing relationships. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
