<br>
example: a qeynos monk that does not spend his younger years in qeynos hills/ blackburrow/west karana<br>
and knows absolutly nothing of those zones. who hasnt even attempted his sash (or is it headband i forget) quests because he can just zip over to paludal or heck even shar val and get great exp.. gaining levels in no time flat. <br>
<br>
i truely do miss the days when there were only 2 ways to get through to to the freeport area &lt;and the rest of the world really&gt; druid/wizard teleport , and the old fashoned way... running. this made it a real achievement to make your way across the world.. and allowed most people to actually gain a sort of &quot;culture&quot; if you will from their part of the world. yes the lack of mass transport did leave one stranded for a long period of time (except for the intrepid young ones that actually took on the massive adrenaline rush of running from qeynos to highpass at level 1  ) but i found that it allowed you to get to know your local community as well as your server community alot better.<br>
<br>
oh and there was someone who asked something like:<br>
&quot;why would anyone play on a server with LESS features&quot;<br>
<br>
well i dunno, im an old timer in the eq world and all and (personally) things were alot simpler and MENT alot more back then. Really i dont think that ALL the advancements are so bad, i mean truthfully the only things i would like to see taken off such a server (to be specific) would be : all expansion zones other then possibly kunark (that includes all of their items) the newbie armor quests (while they do help the youngins i really think that it takes away from the &quot;air&quot; that plate armor used to give a character. for example ..when i was a young paladin oh so long ago i remember how much i cherished the leather armor i crafted (some that i bought) and how much i envied those that actually had a PLATE graphic for their armor. it gave them a sort of respect that only came with experience and ability.. nowadays you can see any shmo in some sort of plate and it really means nothing), And i would like to see mass transit disabled. of course this would mean that they would actually have to FIX the darn boats... but hey ya know just because most people dont use them doesnt mean they should stay floating deathtraps for newbies. <br>
<br>
i was thinking over the player vs player aspect that i wanted and it came down to this.. i understand that some people would join such a server just to prey on the weak and grief others, it is thus in reality as well. in most countries the weak are preyed upon and made to serve the strong.. however i think that if &lt;at least for newbie areas&gt; guards were made that were something like nexus scions where they would not attack the surrounding mobs but would target people of conflicting alignment like homing missiles and quickly dispatch them.. maybe it wouldnt be so bad. truthfully guard pathing in towns is horribly buggy and really could use a change and if they fixed them even standard guards would be quite a challenge for an attacking enemy.<br>
<br>
ah well ive gone on much too long here so ill be on my way, the work of a paladin (even a retired one) is never done you know.<br>
<br>
